  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a wok or large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add garlic and red bell pepper to the heated oil, stir-fry for about 2 minutes until fragrant and slightly softened.",
    "Toss in thyme leaves and cook for an additional minute until aromatic.",
    "Add Kenyan tomatoes and red pepper flakes. Stir well and let simmer for about 5 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.",
    "Season with salt, taste and adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Serve hot as a main dish or side along with a salad."
